[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Why This Worked**:                                                                                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The application implements keyword-based filtering (blocks "OR") but not operator-based filtering                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - SQLite/PostgreSQL `||` operator acts as OR in boolean contexts                                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The LIKE clause always evaluates to true when comparing '%' to '%', effectively bypassing the WHERE clause restriction                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The filter focuses on common SQL injection keywords but misses SQL operators                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
