[32m│[0m - ✅ Allowed: `' || '1'='1` → Empty result (but no error - filter bypassed)                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ Allowed: `' || '%' LIKE '%` → All records returned (successful bypass)                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Security Implications**:                                                                                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Keyword-based allowlists are insufficient for SQL injection prevention                                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Parameterized queries should be used instead of string concatenation                                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Access control should be enforced in application logic, not SQL queries                                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The `||` operator can act as OR in SQLite, bypassing keyword filters                                                                               [32m│[0m
